  "label": "Alcove Bedchamber",
  "description": "This narrow bedchamber occupies the sleeping alcove cut into Cindervale’s reused ashlar, where patched blocks and riveted iron straps remain visible beneath smoke-darkened limewash. A low cot and a rope-strung pallet stand beneath a canvas screen that turns the hearth’s glow into a dull, ember-colored light. Wall niches serve as built-in storage, their edges chipped and soot-scored from long habitation. The air holds coal-smoke and lime dust, and sound transmits clearly through the thick masonry into the surrounding works.",
